Functions:
    A function is reusable code.We can use the function any Where in program.
Syntax:
Function function_name(parameters){
}
 Example:
 function yash(){
        document.write("Hello This is the Function.....")
       }
       yash()// this is function calling
Output:
Hello This is the Function..…
Example:
 function yash(){
        document.write("Hello This is the Function.....","<br>")
       }
       yash()
       document.write("Hello yash","<br>")
       yash()
Output:
Hello This is the Function.....
Hello yash
Hello This is the Function..…
Example: Adding two numbers using function.
function yash(a,b){
        document.write(a+b)
      }
      let a=parseInt(prompt("Enter the 1st number:"))
      let b=parseInt(prompt("Enter the 2nd number:"))
      yash(a,b)
Output:
A=5
B=6
11
